transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Hi, I'd like to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay, what's your name and date of birth?

Speaker 2: My name is Russ Oesterling, O-E-S-T-E-R-L-I-N-G, and it's 5-16-56.

Speaker 1: Okay, what's going on? Is it that you have enough supply at this time?

Speaker 2: I just don't need it anymore.

Speaker 1: At all? Or just for the maintenance?

Speaker 2: No, I don't need it anymore.

Speaker 1: Okay, because what I can go ahead and do for you is that I can go ahead and just pause your prescription.

Speaker 2: I can pause it for half a year in case you need any supply.

Speaker 1: No, why don't you just cancel it, please?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Just be aware that once I cancel it, that means that you will no longer be able to reorder with us, okay?

Speaker 2: And we are the only company who sells FDA-approved Viagra.

Speaker 1: That would be great.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, you're all set.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome. Have a good day.
